args:
The prince and his allies are staying in the Holy
City of Grams when a mysterious group of
androids invades. The Grams army makes no
effort to protect the slums where the poor
reside, so the prince and his allies decide to
fight the invaders in their place.
Please note that this story containers spoilers\nfor Chapters 11 and 14 of the main campaign.
Condition clear. Checking Orchis System.\nSystem clear.
Confirmed. 901 leader, designation\nEirene: Give your situation report.

The 901st Android Corps, including this
unit, designation Eirene, have completed
reactivation. No issues detected in
functionality.
Our orders from the Humanoid Liberation\nAgency are unchanged. You are to\ncommence operations at once.
Do this for the future of all humanoid life,\nand for Ex Machina.
For the future of all humanoid life,\nand for Ex Machina.
Why would they be invading\nthe Holy City of Grams?

▷Laxi, those androids...◁
Commands do not appear to be reaching
them. They must be part of a different
chain of command.

Save the questions for later, Mascula!
Right now, we need to protect everybody
here—and it looks like force is going to
be our only option on that front.
Command transmission is complete, Finni.\nCommence the operation.
State your reason for disobeying orders.

I don't like doing boring things, and it's
SUPER boring to eliminate terrestrials who
just run away all the time. You should
make one of the generic androids do it.
That's quite enough out of you, Finni.

This order comes from Anassa, meaning it
is the will of the Humanoid Liberation
Agency—and you know full well that
androids are not allowed to refuse orders.

If they don't want us refusing orders,
they should make us more obedient.
I mean, don't give us hearts if you don't
want us using 'em, you know?
Finni, that's— Hold on, I'm receiving\na transmission. What?
Huh? Are you saying there are androids\nsiding with terrestrials?
It certainly appears that way, yes.\nBut it shouldn't be possible...
Well, this sounds like a LOT more fun\nthan hunting down a bunch of slugabed\nterrestrials. I'm headin' out!
This never ends! C'mon, Laxi, you're the\nandroid commander, right? Can't you\ncall off the dogs here?
No. I believe they are models from\na thousand years ago.
▷Yep. The original androids were\nanti-dragon weapons originally created\na millennium ago.◁
If I recall correctly, an engineer from the\nEmpire built you 300 years ago based on\nthose much older models.
That's right. The models I'm able to\ncommand are limited to those built by\nMaestro.
▷Oh, and you should be aware that the\noriginal models are far more advanced\nthan those from our era.◁
▷This likely means their core specs\nare higher as well, so you'll need to\nbe extra careful.◁
Damage minimal. I am well.\nLaunching counter-attack.
Whoa, you really ARE allied with the\nterrestrials—which means I can go\nall-out and totally destroy you!
Oh, you're no ordinary scrub...and I love it!\nBut let's see if you can handle THIS!
Positional data lost!\n▷Laxi, above us! Eight o'clock!◁
Not bad, bud! I didn't think you'd be\nable to avoid that one.
▷I'll track the enemy's movements\nwhile you focus on attacking, Laxi.◁\nUnderstood. I'll leave that to you.
Uh...are you talking to yourself\nor something there, bud?
Oh Eirene, you came, too, huh.\nI don't wanna sound like a big oinky hog,\nbut this one's mine, so don't cut in.
That android is clearly in possession of\ntwo hearts...but HOW?
If I can learn how that works,\nperhaps...
Finni, I order you to capture that android.\nDo not destroy it under any circumstances.
If I suspect you are about to destroy\nthe android, I will shut you down.
All units, this is 901 leader.\nResetting target. Commence operation.

{player_name}, we surmise that
android is the leader.
▷If we stop her, we should be able to
stop this fight!◁
Afraid we can't JUST worry about that\none particular android lady.

Grams' army is only deploying to the
rich areas of town, which means the
poor folks here in the slums are gonna
be slaughtered.
Then we'll protect this district ourselves.
